# Spec-Driven Scaffolding

## Directory Structure

Generate a feature-based structure with a **specs directory** at the root:

### Web App (React/Next.js/Vue)

```
specs/                            # Single source of truth
  api/
    openapi.yaml                  # REST API specification
  schemas/
    user.schema.json              # Data contracts
    shared/
      error.schema.json
      pagination.schema.json
  features/
    auth.feature                  # Behavior specifications
  ui/
    button.props.ts               # UI component contracts
  decisions/
    001-tech-stack.md             # ADRs
src/
  app/                            # Routes and pages
  features/                       # Feature modules
    auth/
      components/
      hooks/
      services/
      types.ts                    # Generated from specs/schemas/
      index.ts
    dashboard/
      ...
  shared/
    components/                   # Reusable UI components
    hooks/                        # Shared hooks
    lib/                          # Utility functions
    types/                        # Shared types (generated from specs)
  infrastructure/
    api/                          # API client (generated from OpenAPI)
    config/                       # App configuration
    providers/                    # Context providers
public/                           # Static assets
tests/
  conformance/                    # Spec conformance tests
  e2e/                            # E2E tests from behavior specs
```

### Backend API (Node.js/Python/Go)

```
specs/                            # Single source of truth
  api/
    openapi.yaml
  schemas/
    user.schema.json
    order.schema.json
    shared/
      error.schema.json
      pagination.schema.json
  contracts/
    payment-api.pact.json         # Integration contracts
  features/
    auth.feature
    checkout.feature
  decisions/
    001-database-choice.md
src/
  features/                       # Feature modules
    users/
      controller.ts
      service.ts
      repository.ts
      schema.ts                   # Derived from specs/schemas/
      routes.ts                   # Derived from specs/api/
      __tests__/
        conformance/              # Spec conformance tests
        unit/
    orders/
      ...
  shared/
    middleware/                    # Express/Fastify middleware
    errors/                       # Error classes matching error contract
    utils/                        # Utility functions
    types/                        # Types generated from specs
  infrastructure/
    database/                     # DB connection, migrations
    cache/                        # Cache layer
    config/                       # Environment config
    logger/                       # Structured logging
```

### Fullstack (Monorepo)

```
specs/                            # Shared specs across apps
  api/
  schemas/
  contracts/
  features/
  decisions/
apps/
  web/                            # Frontend app
  api/                            # Backend app
  mobile/                         # Mobile app (optional)
packages/
  shared/                         # Shared types (generated from specs)
  ui/                             # Shared component library
  config/                         # Shared configurations
```

## Tooling Setup Checklist

For every project, set up:

- [ ] **Package manager**: npm/pnpm/yarn (JS), uv/poetry (Python), go mod (Go).
- [ ] **Linter**: ESLint (JS/TS), Ruff (Python), golangci-lint (Go), clippy (Rust).
- [ ] **Formatter**: Prettier (JS/TS), Black/Ruff (Python), gofmt (Go), rustfmt (Rust).
- [ ] **Type checker**: TypeScript strict mode, mypy/pyright (Python).
- [ ] **Test runner**: Vitest/Jest (JS), pytest (Python), go test (Go), cargo test (Rust).
- [ ] **Spec linter**: `spectral` (OpenAPI), `ajv` (JSON Schema), `asyncapi-cli` (AsyncAPI).
- [ ] **Conformance tester**: `dredd`/`prism`/`schemathesis` (API), `pact` (contracts).
- [ ] **Code generator**: `openapi-generator`/`orval` (types from specs).
- [ ] **Git hooks**: Husky + lint-staged (JS), pre-commit (Python) — include spec linting.
- [ ] **Environment**: `.env.example` with all variables documented.
- [ ] **Editor config**: `.editorconfig` for consistent formatting across editors.

## Configuration Files

Generate appropriate config files for the chosen stack:

### JavaScript/TypeScript
- `package.json` with scripts: dev, build, test, lint, format, `spec:lint`, `spec:test`, `spec:generate`.
- `tsconfig.json` with strict mode enabled.
- `.eslintrc` or `eslint.config.js` with recommended rules.
- `.prettierrc` with consistent settings.
- `.spectral.yaml` for OpenAPI linting rules.

### Python
- `pyproject.toml` with all tool configuration.
- `requirements.txt` or `uv.lock` for pinned dependencies.
- `schemathesis` config for API conformance testing.

### Go
- `go.mod` with module path.
- `Makefile` with build, test, lint, `spec-lint`, `spec-test` targets.

### Rust
- `Cargo.toml` with workspace configuration.
- `clippy.toml` for custom lint rules.

## Initial Files

Create these files at project setup:
- `README.md` — project purpose, setup instructions, spec overview.
- `.gitignore` — stack-appropriate ignore patterns.
- `.env.example` — all environment variables with descriptions.
- `specs/api/openapi.yaml` — initial API spec skeleton.
- `specs/schemas/shared/error.schema.json` — standard error envelope contract.
- `specs/schemas/shared/pagination.schema.json` — standard pagination contract.
- `specs/decisions/001-tech-stack.md` — first ADR: technology selection.
- `Dockerfile` — if containerization is needed.
- `docker-compose.yml` — for local development with services (DB, cache, etc.).

## First Commit Checklist

The first commit should include:
- [ ] Project structure created with `specs/` directory.
- [ ] Initial spec skeleton (OpenAPI, shared schemas, error contract).
- [ ] Spec linting configured and passing.
- [ ] All configuration files in place.
- [ ] Dependencies installed and lockfile committed.
- [ ] Linter and formatter running without errors.
- [ ] At least one conformance test skeleton passing.
- [ ] README with setup instructions and spec overview.
- [ ] CI pipeline configuration (including spec validation step).
